# English Identifiers

All code naming must be English.

## Must be English

- Variables, constants, functions, classes, types, interfaces, props
- File and folder names, feature names, route segments
- Schema fields that are code identifiers (not user-facing copy)

## Portuguese is allowed only in

- UI strings / user-facing copy
- Product comments aimed at end users (when the product is PT)
- User-facing documentation

## Examples

```typescript
// BAD
const usuario = ...
function buscarDados() {}
type Pedido = ...
// feature folder: src/features/pedidos

// GOOD
const user = ...
function fetchData() {}
type Order = ...
// feature folder: src/features/orders
```
